Canadian Overseas Petroleum, RIM: Canadian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a t t   W a l c o f f
-- 
2011-06-30T21:30:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/canadian-overseas-petroleum-rim-canadian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Canadian trading July 4. Canadian
markets are closed tomorrow for the Canada Day holiday.  Canadian Overseas Petroleum Ltd. (XOP)  : The oil and gas
explorer said it expects Liberia to approve its proposed $85
million purchase of an offshore block in the third quarter. The
company said in May that the acquisition should close around
June 30.  Research In Motion Ltd. (RIM)  : The BlackBerry maker said
a committee of independent directors will study the company’s
corporate governance structure. Northwest & Ethical Investments
LP will withdraw a proposal to separate the roles of chairman
and chief executive officer from RIM’s annual meeting agenda.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Matt Walcoff at   mwalcoff1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
